{
  "text": "With those preliminaries, we are now ready to ask the usual √ s min question: Given the measured values of E (up) , E (sub) , P (up) and P (sub) , what is the minimum value √ s (sub) min of the subsystem Mandelstam invariant mass variable √ s (sub) , which is consistent with those measurements? Proceeding as in [CITATION_1] , once again we find a very simple universal answer, which, with the help of (3.3) and (3.4), can be equivalently written in several different ways as follows: [CITATION_2] where in the last line we have introduced the Lorentz 1+2 vectors",
